	<div id="en301549-content">
		<h1>EN 301 549: European Accessibility Standard</h1>
	
	<p>EN 301 549 is a European standard that specifies the functional accessibility requirements for Information and Communication Technology (ICT) products and services. This standard is crucial for ensuring digital accessibility across the European Union and has become a benchmark for accessibility compliance worldwide.</p>
	
	<h2>What is EN 301 549?</h2>
	<p>EN 301 549 is a harmonized European standard that defines the accessibility requirements for ICT products and services. It was developed by the European Telecommunications Standards Institute (ETSI) and is based on the Web Content Accessibility Guidelines (WCAG) 2.1, along with additional requirements specific to ICT products.</p>
	
	<h2>Key Requirements</h2>
	<p>The standard covers various aspects of digital accessibility including:</p>
	<ul>
		<li>Perceivable content and user interface components</li>
		<li>Operable user interface components and navigation</li>
		<li>Understandable information and user interface operation</li>
		<li>Robust content that can be interpreted by assistive technologies</li>
		<li>Documentation and support services accessibility</li>
	</ul>
	
	<h2>Compliance Levels</h2>
	<p>EN 301 549 defines three levels of compliance:</p>
	<ul>
		<li><strong>Level A:</strong> Basic accessibility requirements</li>
		<li><strong>Level AA:</strong> Enhanced accessibility requirements (most commonly required)</li>
		<li><strong>Level AAA:</strong> Highest level of accessibility requirements</li>
	</ul>
	
	<h2>Impact on Web Development</h2>
	<p>For web developers and designers, understanding EN 301 549 is essential for creating accessible digital experiences. The standard provides clear guidelines for implementing accessibility features such as keyboard navigation, screen reader compatibility, color contrast, and alternative text for images.</p>
	
	<p>This standard is particularly important for organizations doing business in the European Union, as it forms the basis for accessibility requirements in public procurement and helps ensure compliance with the European Accessibility Act.</p>
